```

**Note:** You'll need to create these template files for user_data:

**user_data_blue.tpl:**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Blue Environment</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

**user_data_green.tpl:**
```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Green Environment</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

Replace `"example.com"` in the Route 53 zone data source with your actual hosted zone name. The configuration sets up blue as primary with failover to green if health checks fail.

