1. Replace `https://github.com/your-org/course-repo.git` with your actual course repository
2. Set up GitHub personal access token in AWS CodeBuild source credentials
3. Trigger builds by calling the CodeBuild project with environment variables:
   - `STUDENT_REPO_URL`: Student GitHub repo URL
   - `STUDENT_BRANCH`: Branch to test (default: main)
4. Results stored in S3 bucket with repo-name prefixed paths
5. Customize `buildspec` for your specific grading requirements (Python, Java, etc.)

